{
  "document_id": "col-33",
  "title": "Colossians 33",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "No evil will befall the one who fears the Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "The wise will not hate the law,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "The sensible person will trust in the law,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Prepare what to say, and then you will be listened to;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "The heart of a fool is like a cart wheel"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "A mocking friend is like a stallion"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Why is one day more important than another,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "By the Lord’s wisdom they were distinguished,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "Some days he exalted and hallowed,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "All humans come from the ground,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "In the fullness of his knowledge the Lord distinguished them"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Some he blessed and exalted,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Like clay in the hand of the potter,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "Good is the opposite of evil"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Look at all the works of the Most High;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "Now I was the last to keep vigil;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "by the blessing of the Lord I arrived first,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Consider that I have not labored for myself alone"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "Hear me, you who are great among the people,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "To son or wife, to brother or friend,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "While you are still alive and have breath in you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "For it is better that your children should ask from you"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Excel in all that you do;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "At the time when you end the days of your life,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Fodder and a stick and burdens for a donkey;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "Set your slaves to work, and you will find rest;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "Yoke and strap will bow the neck,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "Put them to work in order that they may not be idle,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "for idleness teaches much evil."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "Set them to work as is fitting for them,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "If you have but one slave, treat him like yourself,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "If you ill-treat him and he leaves you and runs away,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-33-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "which way will you go to seek him?"
    }
  ]
}